5 years in the books with IM! 🙏🏼🥂

I’m writing this as I watch the sunset in Laguna beach thanking God for leading the way. What a ride it’s been so far. I came here 5 years ago committed to the long haul. God pointed me in the right direction and I took action. 

It was late 2017 that Britt and I started praying for an opportunity where we would be able to achieve a lifestyle of freedom for us and our future family, but also a company we could rest our head at night knowing the ownership has the fields best interest at heart and that’s exactly what we got with IM. 

For years, I wondered if I could ever hit it big and live a great life like some of these top guys. I mean, I always believed in myself but you still wonder. 💭 

Has it all been sunshine and rainbows? Shi*%… Nope.. It’s been a wild ride to say the least, but isn’t that life? Isn’t that business? I would say so. I didn’t get to high in the highs, and didn’t get too low in the lows. Steady Eddy is the way I rock. You find the learning lessons from L’s and you keep moving forward. 

All summed up, this company changed my families life forever.  No place I’d rather be. 

Cheers to the next 5! 🥂

Life is too short not to love what you do. If you don't wake up with a fire in your belly, and a burning white hot desire to start your day off, you may want to re-evaluate things.

When we find are true soul mate, mission, or purpose in life it's incredible how our lives transcend to heights we could never imagine!

"When you are inspired by some great purpose, some extraordinary purpose, all your thoughts break their bounds. Your mind transcends limitations, your consciousness expands in every direction and you find yourself in a new, great, and wonderful world. Dormant forces, faculties and talents become alive, and you discover yourself to be a greater person by far than you ever dreamed yourself to be." - Patanjali

At the end of the day, the true measure of success is simply waking up every day and loving WHAT you do, and WHO you do it with!
No complaints.🤍

Live a life by design, not by default. 👏🏼👏🏼

Most people live by default meaning, they are reacting to what’s happening to them while it’s happening. They don’t take any control of their lives, they just go through it experiencing whatever is thrown at them and feeling there is nothing they can do about it. 

Living by design in comparison, is doing whatever you can to take charge of your life. We have one shot on this planet, don’t settle for anything less than everything you ever dreamed of! ✨🦋♾️⚡️

The price you will pay to make your dreams come true is far less than the price you will pay if you don't.

Deciding not to take on difficult challenges is a CHOICE.

And usually, it's one filled with REGRETS.
Unfortunately, you can't see how bad you'll feel about missed opportunities until they are long gone in your rear-view mirror.

TAKE CHANCES.
TRY HARD STUFF.
FAIL OFTEN.

One way or another, you're going to ante up with effort or remorse, so you might as well PAY THE PRICE and chase your DREAMS.

You don’t need physical eyes to see the life you desire. You need your spiritual eyes to see the life you desire, and you do this through the power of imagination. 

1. Eliminate the thoughts that done serve you, and replace them with your goals dreams and visions. 

2. Stare at your goals repeatedly because when you do this, your RAS begins unconsciously to help filter into your existence the people, places, conversations, and things to help materialize that space that you created with the thought.

3. Exercise repetition. Your brain literally gravitates towards which its most familiar with and begins to believe you really belong in your dreams. 

4. Control the beginning and end of the day. Start your day off with a little meditation visualizing what you want your life to look like. So now your sub consious begins to actively help align the opportunities in your life. Same with when you go to bed. Focus on your goals and while you sleep your sub concious is working to make it real in your mind. 

This isn’t new material. It’s been around for centuries. You become what you think about most of the time. You possess what you obsess!

Write this down. “The best place to find an ACE is in the mirror.”

YOU are the ace you are looking for… In order to recruit an ace you need to become one first.

What does it looks like to be an ACE? ⬇️⬇️⬇️

1. Burning desire - Aces aren’t
hoping to succeed, they aren’t interested in succeeding… they are absolutely burning alive to the core to win. 

2. Aces EXPECT to win at the highest level. MJ might not have been the best 3 point shooter, best passer, or even the best ball handler, but he absolutely EXPECTED to win and that was the great separator. 

3. Aces deal with adversity different than non aces deal with adversity. “It’s not about how hard you can hit… it’s about how hard you can get hit and keep moving forward!” 🥊 

Im gonna say something, which for many of you - might be everything. If you and I were to sit together alone with no one around. Your upline isn’t around, your team isn’t around, your family isn’t around.. Deep deep down… There’s a lot of you that truly don’t believe you are going to win. You are treating IM like a lottery ticket. You hope to win. It would be cooool if you win. You would like to win. But deep deep deep down you believe you aren’t the type of person that’s going to win. 

LET ME TELL YOU SOMETHING.. if that’s your belief, you got no shot. Everything you are believing in that regard, is a lie from the enemy. And the truth is this… You are designed to be a champion, and that is your destiny and it’s time to turn the lies off and listen to the voice of truth in your life. Become the ACE you are called to be, and don’t settle for anything less than everything you desire. Let’s get to work! 👊🏼

1. ELIMINATE the negative thoughts that aren’t serving you and replace them with your goals, visions, and dreams.

2. Stare at your goals repeatedly. When you do this is your RAS begins unconsciously to help filter into your existence the people, places, conversations, and things to help materialize that space that you created with the thought.
